---
import CapabilityBlock from './CapabilityBlock.astro'
import GridCTA from '../primitives/GridCTA.astro'
---

<div id="why" class="why-section px-responsive-md py-responsive-lg">
    <div class="why-header">
      <h2 class="why-headline">
        Not Just a Developer. Hands-On CTO With Business & UX Understanding.
      </h2>
      <p class="why-subhead">
        Where others need specialized teams, I bring broad-horizon expertise
        across the entire technical stack - plus business strategy and user
        experience perspective.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="cards-grid">
      <CapabilityBlock title="Complete Technical Capabilities">
        <h4>What makes this possible:</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Programming:</strong> TypeScript, Python, Bash - full-stack web,
            IoT, automation
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>DevOps:</strong> CI/CD pipelines, cloud infrastructure, Docker,
            deployment automation
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>IoT & Robotics:</strong> Hardware integration, firmware, sensor
            systems, ROS
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>UX/Design:</strong> Interface design, information architecture,
            user-centered thinking
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Product & Business:</strong> Marketing background, sales experience,
            business coaching training
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Leadership:</strong> Team assessment, assembly, and management
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="value-statement">
          <strong>The value:</strong> You get someone who understands the complete
          picture - from business requirements through technical architecture to
          user experience. One person with the perspective of an entire technical
          team.
        </p>
      </CapabilityBlock>

      <CapabilityBlock title="Corporate Experience, Independent Execution">
        <h4>20+ years building complex systems:</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>BSH</strong> (Bosch Siemens Hausgeräte) - Smart home appliances
            firmware
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Cheil Poland</strong> (Samsung subsidiary) - Humanoid robotics
            prototypes
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Ubudu</strong> (French IoT startup) - RTLS systems deployed worldwide
          </li>
          <li>Multiple product development roles across industries</li>
        </ul>
        <h4 class="mt-2">Why independent:</h4>
        <p>
          I couldn't advance to higher leadership positions within corporate
          structures (limited roles, politics), so I build innovation teams for
          others instead. You get corporate-grade expertise with startup
          agility.
        </p>
      </CapabilityBlock>

      <CapabilityBlock title="From Vision to Working Team">
        <h4>I don't just consult. I build.</h4>
        <h5>My process:</h5>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <strong>Vision & Architecture</strong> - Technical strategy, system design,
            foundation
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Prototype Development</strong> - Working, usable prototypes demonstrating
            value
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Team Assembly</strong> (if needed) - Assessment, hiring, and team
            building
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Knowledge Transfer</strong> - Your team gains ownership, capabilities
            remain
          </li>
        </ol>
        <p class="value-statement">
          <strong>The result:</strong> You go from "nothing" to "working solution
          with team in place" to continue independently.
        </p>
      </CapabilityBlock>
    </div>

    <GridCTA
      href="/portfolio"
      text="View Complete Portfolio"
      icon="folder"
      variant="secondary"
    />
  </div>
</div>
